1
00:00:38,927 --> 00:00:42,237
Willard! Bring in
the videocassette recorder.

2
00:01:17,327 --> 00:01:21,240
Suddenly, l realized that,
l don't have a pension plan...

3
00:01:21,327 --> 00:01:24,876
...l don't have a health plan,
l don't have a dental plan...

4
00:01:24,967 --> 00:01:26,525
...l don't have....

5
00:02:17,087 --> 00:02:18,315
Willard!

6
00:02:27,727 --> 00:02:29,604
Where the hell is my blue hat?

7
00:02:29,687 --> 00:02:31,837
l don't know, Miss Crock.

8
00:02:31,967 --> 00:02:35,437
Do you expect me to go
to my 10:00 meeting, like this?

9
00:02:36,447 --> 00:02:38,881
No. Absolutely not, Miss Crock.

10
00:02:38,967 --> 00:02:40,605
l'll help you find it.

11
00:02:49,207 --> 00:02:50,435
l'm cold!

12
00:02:51,167 --> 00:02:54,204
You taking a coffee break, lazybones?

13
00:02:54,487 --> 00:02:56,921
All right, it's a good job.

14
00:02:57,927 --> 00:03:00,236
l should have known it was you.

15
00:03:13,207 --> 00:03:16,438
Miss Crock, you have such an appreciation
of fine clothing...

16
00:03:16,527 --> 00:03:19,121
...l was thinking it was time
you buy me a new uniform.

17
00:03:19,207 --> 00:03:22,244
You lookjust fine to me, Willard.

18
00:03:22,687 --> 00:03:24,279
And you're dismissed.

19
00:03:24,567 --> 00:03:26,285
But, it's disintegrating.

20
00:03:26,487 --> 00:03:28,557
The buttons are barely hanging on.

21
00:03:28,767 --> 00:03:30,837
Willard, that is a terrific suit.

22
00:03:31,007 --> 00:03:34,124
Your father worked for me for 30 years.
Wore that suit every day.

23
00:03:34,207 --> 00:03:35,606
Never complained!

24
00:03:35,687 --> 00:03:37,120
Yeah, and then he died.

25
00:03:37,207 --> 00:03:40,756
And then, at the funeral, you made
the undertaker give it back to you...

26
00:03:40,847 --> 00:03:43,407
...so you could stick me in it
for another 15 years.

27
00:03:43,487 --> 00:03:45,557
Just what are you implying?

28
00:03:46,527 --> 00:03:51,043
Miss Crock, it's Christmas time.
l'm only asking for a new uniform.

29
00:03:51,127 --> 00:03:53,197
''Only'' a new uniform?

30
00:03:53,487 --> 00:03:56,524
And pretty soon it'll be
''only'' a new broom, maybe.

31
00:03:56,807 --> 00:04:00,641
And before you know it,
l will be ''only'' bankrupt!

32
00:04:01,447 --> 00:04:04,405
Now, would you please
get out of my sight...

33
00:04:04,807 --> 00:04:08,117
...before l kick you in the ass?

34
00:04:21,767 --> 00:04:25,157
lt's not my fault
you have frost on your strawberries.

35
00:04:25,247 --> 00:04:27,363
We have a contract.

36
00:04:28,007 --> 00:04:31,556
Well then, l'll see you in court.

37
00:04:32,407 --> 00:04:33,806
Excuse me, ma'am.

38
00:04:34,567 --> 00:04:36,319
-l've got the Danish.
-Okay.

39
00:04:36,447 --> 00:04:38,085
Bring 'em in.

40
00:04:38,727 --> 00:04:40,479
Miss Crock, l'd like you to meet...

41
00:04:40,567 --> 00:04:44,606
...Gunn Froling, Erland Vetterlund,
Per Malmsjo and Bertil Guve.

42
00:04:44,687 --> 00:04:46,882
The executive team
from Copenhagen Snak Food.

43
00:04:46,967 --> 00:04:51,085
Well, l'm just flattered that you're
even considering my little factory.

44
00:04:51,847 --> 00:04:52,916
Lovely output.

45
00:04:53,007 --> 00:04:55,840
That's terrific, Gunn.
You are truly a Great Dane.

46
00:04:59,527 --> 00:05:03,440
Come, gentlemen, l'd like to show you
the Bun room. l'm sure you'll love it.

47
00:05:05,127 --> 00:05:07,197
lt's just past Jellies and Creams.

48
00:05:07,607 --> 00:05:09,438
What a bunch of bores!

49
00:05:10,327 --> 00:05:12,238
l never know what those guys are saying.

50
00:05:12,327 --> 00:05:14,887
Never mind about that.
Do you think we've got a deal?

51
00:05:14,967 --> 00:05:17,083
Does Big Boy have a weight problem?

52
00:05:17,367 --> 00:05:20,120
Soon you're going to be
the richest, prettiest...

53
00:05:20,367 --> 00:05:24,280
...sexiest lady in the entire pastry industry.

54
00:05:24,687 --> 00:05:26,279
l've told you, Chip...

55
00:05:27,407 --> 00:05:29,045
...not in the office.

56
00:05:49,087 --> 00:05:50,281
Hey, guys.

57
00:05:52,847 --> 00:05:56,078
Nothing says Christmas Eve
like some hot, spicy chicken wings.

58
00:05:56,167 --> 00:05:57,725
All right!

59
00:06:00,367 --> 00:06:03,279
lf they're so yummy, how come
you only show up when it's free?

60
00:06:04,367 --> 00:06:05,516
There he is.

61
00:06:05,727 --> 00:06:06,398
About time!

62
00:06:06,487 --> 00:06:09,479
Can you believe it? The old prune
made me clean her chimney.

63
00:06:09,567 --> 00:06:12,081
Like she thinks Santa's coming
to pay her a visit.

64
00:06:15,247 --> 00:06:18,319
Now, look here. Be careful with this
'cause it's kind of strong.

65
00:06:22,967 --> 00:06:25,481
Willard, you need to make
a New Year's resolution.

66
00:06:25,567 --> 00:06:27,603
Quit working for the ball-buster.

67
00:06:27,687 --> 00:06:30,599
Show her who's boss, man.
Take a shit in her soup.

68
00:06:30,967 --> 00:06:32,844
Thanks. That's real constructive.

69
00:06:32,927 --> 00:06:35,999
You know how things are today.
A man has a job, he holds onto it.

70
00:06:36,087 --> 00:06:38,442
ln your case, till he dies of old age.

71
00:06:38,527 --> 00:06:40,563
Yeah, like my old man.

72
00:06:42,167 --> 00:06:44,556
You know what he said to me
on his deathbed?

73
00:06:44,647 --> 00:06:47,480
He said, ''Stick with Miss Crock.
You'll get ahead.''

74
00:06:47,567 --> 00:06:49,876
l don't know what he was talking about.

75
00:06:50,967 --> 00:06:53,117
Merry Christmas, Willard.

76
00:06:53,887 --> 00:06:55,923
Merry Christmas, Rusty.

77
00:06:56,007 --> 00:06:58,282
''Good King Wenceslas looked out

78
00:06:58,447 --> 00:07:00,677
''On the Feast of Stephen''

79
00:07:00,847 --> 00:07:02,565
Oh, Chip...

80
00:07:03,247 --> 00:07:04,999
...it's beautiful!

81
00:07:05,087 --> 00:07:06,884
Now open yours.

82
00:07:07,127 --> 00:07:08,924
l'm so excited.

83
00:07:09,367 --> 00:07:12,723
Oh, Virginia, what a sweet gift!

84
00:07:12,927 --> 00:07:16,397
l know how much you like money.
lt's $50,000.

85
00:07:16,487 --> 00:07:18,842
You can buy anything you want with it.

86
00:07:20,607 --> 00:07:23,405
What are you standing around for, Willard?

87
00:07:23,487 --> 00:07:26,923
We don't want a mess now,
do we, on Christmas?

88
00:07:38,447 --> 00:07:41,519
-Will that be all?
-That will not be all.

89
00:07:47,327 --> 00:07:49,204
Merry Christmas.

90
00:07:51,127 --> 00:07:54,164
Miss Crock, l wasn't expecting this.

91
00:07:54,487 --> 00:07:58,924
l thought of something that l knew
you'd be thrilled to death with!

92
00:07:59,567 --> 00:08:01,842
Miss Crock, God bless you.

93
00:08:01,927 --> 00:08:04,680
-Open it!
-You are a good woman.

94
00:08:06,287 --> 00:08:08,243
-What's this?
-Your favorite.

95
00:08:08,327 --> 00:08:10,636
Mincemeat pie.

96
00:08:11,807 --> 00:08:13,638
Where the hell is my suit?

97
00:08:13,767 --> 00:08:17,396
Goodness gracious! Sakes alive!
l thought you'd like it.

98
00:08:17,487 --> 00:08:19,443
-Like it?
-Yes.

99
00:08:19,527 --> 00:08:23,156
And l put a pair of cuff links in there
as well.

100
00:08:23,567 --> 00:08:25,683
You went all out, didn't you?

101
00:08:25,767 --> 00:08:29,077
A pair of crackerjack cuff links
and one shitty pie!

102
00:08:34,727 --> 00:08:35,955
What are you doing?

103
00:08:36,207 --> 00:08:38,767
l thought we were going
to Leroy's Christmas kegger?

104
00:08:38,847 --> 00:08:41,361
Miss Crock said
l gotta spend a night in the box.

105
00:08:41,447 --> 00:08:44,007
Damn! lt's more like in Filipino prison.

106
00:08:44,287 --> 00:08:47,484
-''Get in that sweatbox!''
-Leave me alone!

107
00:08:48,807 --> 00:08:49,796
Fine.

108
00:08:52,367 --> 00:08:54,005
Feliz Navidad.

109
00:08:57,887 --> 00:09:00,117
Just in case you get hungry.

110
00:09:10,767 --> 00:09:12,837
Beat it. This is my dinner.

111
00:09:15,447 --> 00:09:17,358
You rat, l'll squash you.

112
00:09:19,967 --> 00:09:21,366
Come here.

113
00:09:29,327 --> 00:09:33,036
l can't believe l've tolerated him
for as long as l have.

114
00:09:33,247 --> 00:09:36,000
He's just a user.
Willard's exploited your generosity.

115
00:09:36,087 --> 00:09:38,203
That's exactly right.

116
00:09:38,487 --> 00:09:41,559
l mean his father, Teddy, was a nice man.

117
00:09:41,647 --> 00:09:44,002
-But enough is enough.
-Really.

118
00:09:44,167 --> 00:09:46,044
Well, tomorrow, we'll...

119
00:09:46,847 --> 00:09:48,246
...fire him.

120
00:09:48,927 --> 00:09:50,758
Throw his stuff in the furnace.

121
00:09:55,287 --> 00:09:59,644
-Santa Claus must be stopped.
-There will be no Christmas this year.

122
00:09:59,767 --> 00:10:00,995
You got that right.

123
00:10:02,927 --> 00:10:04,679
You're not gonna believe this.

124
00:10:04,767 --> 00:10:06,644
The old grinch is gonna fire me.

125
00:10:06,727 --> 00:10:09,082
lt's ridiculous.
Why would someone fire their slave?

126
00:10:09,167 --> 00:10:12,443
Because she's mean.
She picked Christmas Day to do it.

127
00:10:12,527 --> 00:10:14,757
Damn! You need revenge.

128
00:10:14,887 --> 00:10:20,041
-Revenge! We need revenge!
-Revenge! We need revenge!

129
00:10:20,127 --> 00:10:25,838
Let's kidnap Santa Claus. We'll break
into his toy shop and seize him!

130
00:10:25,967 --> 00:10:28,242
Maybe those moon men are...

131
00:10:29,207 --> 00:10:32,165
-...onto something.
-You mean we should kidnap Santa?

132
00:10:33,167 --> 00:10:35,635
Wait a minute.
Why don't we just kidnap Miss Crock?

133
00:10:35,727 --> 00:10:38,002
-No, it's crazy.
-No, that's brilliant!

134
00:10:38,247 --> 00:10:40,397
We'll grab Granny
and hold her ass for ransom.

135
00:10:40,487 --> 00:10:43,126
And if they don't pay,
we start hacking off her fingers.

136
00:10:43,207 --> 00:10:45,357
First her thumb, then her pointer...

137
00:10:45,567 --> 00:10:47,558
...then her little nasty finger.

138
00:10:47,647 --> 00:10:49,205
What are you talking about?

139
00:10:49,287 --> 00:10:52,723
We're not criminals.
You fry chicken, l drive a car.

140
00:10:53,287 --> 00:10:56,165
When that money comes rolling in,
l'll go crazy, man!

141
00:10:56,247 --> 00:10:58,761
-l'll laminate my menus.
-Shut up, okay?

142
00:10:59,527 --> 00:11:02,087
We know nothing
about kidnapping an old lady.

143
00:11:04,807 --> 00:11:06,126
But what about her dog?

144
00:11:06,207 --> 00:11:07,925
-You mean Biscuit?
-No, Muffin.

145
00:11:09,047 --> 00:11:12,198
Yeah, she loves him
more than anything in the world.

146
00:11:12,287 --> 00:11:15,245
l bet she'd pay plenty
for that old bag of fleas.

147
00:11:15,487 --> 00:11:17,921
Yeah, l bet she'd pay $1 million.

148
00:11:42,927 --> 00:11:45,282
Remember, we have to be quiet
inside the house.

149
00:11:45,367 --> 00:11:47,039
Miss Crock is a light sleeper.

150
00:11:47,127 --> 00:11:49,243
You ain't gotta worry about me.

151
00:11:54,487 --> 00:11:56,603
This place is nice.

152
00:12:00,327 --> 00:12:02,522
What the hell are you doing?

153
00:12:02,887 --> 00:12:05,924
-l'm checking for electric eyes.
-There's no electric eyes.

154
00:12:06,007 --> 00:12:08,441
-How do you know? They're invisible.
-Trust me.

155
00:12:08,527 --> 00:12:10,597
l've lived here my entire life.

156
00:12:16,567 --> 00:12:19,161
So, this is where the old bitch sleeps?

157
00:12:26,527 --> 00:12:28,802
Okay, give me the weenie.

158
00:12:39,967 --> 00:12:42,686
Okay, Muffin.
l gotta special treat for you.

159
00:12:45,327 --> 00:12:46,282
Cripes!

160
00:12:51,287 --> 00:12:53,596
What kind of aim was that?

161
00:12:53,687 --> 00:12:55,040
Muffin!

162
00:12:55,967 --> 00:12:57,685
Bite my weenie.

163
00:13:09,407 --> 00:13:11,477
The hell with this. Plan B.

164
00:13:17,727 --> 00:13:19,763
Will you shut that dog up?

165
00:13:23,687 --> 00:13:25,200
You bastard!

166
00:13:48,247 --> 00:13:50,203
Would you keep it down?

167
00:13:50,407 --> 00:13:53,683
''Keep it down?''
This thing is eating my hand!

168
00:14:00,687 --> 00:14:02,279
Jesus, this is a nightmare!

169
00:14:02,367 --> 00:14:04,085
Put him in the box!

170
00:14:12,567 --> 00:14:15,035
Who's smarter? Now who's smarter?

171
00:14:17,927 --> 00:14:19,599
What should it say?

172
00:14:19,687 --> 00:14:21,200
''We've got him.

173
00:14:21,287 --> 00:14:24,643
''Pay us $1 million, or he's a dead dog!''

174
00:14:25,807 --> 00:14:27,843
-How does that sound?
-Fine.

175
00:14:28,687 --> 00:14:30,040
Let's get the hell out of here.

176
00:14:43,127 --> 00:14:44,879
$1 million!

177
00:14:45,207 --> 00:14:46,959
This is the happiest day of my life.

178
00:14:47,047 --> 00:14:50,164
-With that money, we can do anything.
-l know what l'm gonna do.

179
00:14:50,247 --> 00:14:52,681
l'm gonna buy me a four-star chicken hole.

180
00:14:52,767 --> 00:14:56,123
l'll get a better neighborhood
and a listing in the Zagat Guide.

181
00:14:56,207 --> 00:14:59,995
l'm going someplace warm where you
don't need layered clothing. Start over.

182
00:15:00,087 --> 00:15:02,647
l got some good years left in me.
l can better myself.

183
00:15:02,727 --> 00:15:05,878
l'm gonna register at one of them
four-year universities.

184
00:15:20,367 --> 00:15:21,595
My friend...

185
00:15:21,767 --> 00:15:23,837
...here's to second chances.

186
00:16:24,807 --> 00:16:27,844
Did you have a lovely sleep, Muffin? Yes.

187
00:16:27,967 --> 00:16:31,198
Now, we'll have a lovely breakfast,
you and....

188
00:16:36,567 --> 00:16:40,082
Oh, my God!

189
00:16:41,807 --> 00:16:43,399
Look at me.

190
00:16:43,687 --> 00:16:44,722
Muffin!

191
00:16:45,367 --> 00:16:47,801
Look what they've done to your mother.

192
00:16:48,687 --> 00:16:49,836
l don't know....

193
00:16:52,647 --> 00:16:58,517
''We've got him. Pay us $1 million
or he's a dead dog.''

194
00:16:59,847 --> 00:17:01,599
Who's a dead dog?

195
00:17:02,127 --> 00:17:03,526
Willard?

196
00:17:05,927 --> 00:17:08,077
Man, we've got so many choices.

197
00:17:08,167 --> 00:17:10,886
-l'm just trying to get out of Pittsburgh.
-You said it.

198
00:17:10,967 --> 00:17:13,527
Check out this. Bora Bora.

199
00:17:14,087 --> 00:17:16,647
l was thinking more like Caribbean myself.

200
00:17:16,727 --> 00:17:20,197
Whichever one has a school
with a strong liberal arts program.

201
00:17:22,407 --> 00:17:23,203
Lord! l'm dead!

202
00:17:25,167 --> 00:17:27,317
-We're going to jail.
-What do you mean ''we''?

203
00:17:27,407 --> 00:17:29,682
That's my picture on the front page.

204
00:17:35,927 --> 00:17:39,476
Who would have thought kidnapping a dog
would make the front page?

205
00:17:39,567 --> 00:17:42,923
Wait a minute. They think it was me.
They think l was kidnapped.

206
00:17:43,007 --> 00:17:46,477
-They don't even mention Muffin.
-Why would somebody kidnap you?

207
00:17:46,567 --> 00:17:48,603
l don't know, but they think someone did.

208
00:17:48,687 --> 00:17:51,997
''There were signs of a scuffle,
the chauffeur's blood was on a wall...

209
00:17:52,087 --> 00:17:54,681
''...and a note demanded $1 million...

210
00:17:54,887 --> 00:17:57,355
''...or he's a dead dog.''

211
00:18:11,207 --> 00:18:12,959
Sweet Jesus!

212
00:18:13,687 --> 00:18:15,723
We kidnapped a turd.

213
00:18:15,807 --> 00:18:18,321
According to sources,
the missing chauffeur had been...

214
00:18:18,407 --> 00:18:21,126
...a loyal employee for over 15 years.

215
00:18:21,367 --> 00:18:23,927
Virginia Crock,
known for her mouthwatering treats...

216
00:18:24,007 --> 00:18:27,238
...awoke this morning
to news that was not so sweet.

217
00:18:39,567 --> 00:18:41,319
Do you have any enemies?

218
00:18:41,407 --> 00:18:45,685
Not that l know of.
l'm just an elderly lady who makes pies.

219
00:18:45,887 --> 00:18:49,800
Well, does Mr. Fillmore have any enemies?

220
00:18:50,327 --> 00:18:53,080
-Who?
-That's Willard's last name.

221
00:18:56,367 --> 00:18:57,641
Not that l know of.

222
00:18:57,727 --> 00:19:01,276
Did he have anybody
that he used to bring around the house?

223
00:19:02,127 --> 00:19:03,606
Not that l know of.

224
00:19:05,167 --> 00:19:07,397
Does he have any living relatives?

225
00:19:07,487 --> 00:19:09,125
Not that l know of.

226
00:19:12,607 --> 00:19:13,642
Ma'am...

227
00:19:15,167 --> 00:19:16,964
...excuse me, but...

228
00:19:17,247 --> 00:19:20,239
...this man worked for you
for over a decade...

229
00:19:20,367 --> 00:19:24,724
...and you don't know
if he has any friends or any relatives?

230
00:19:24,807 --> 00:19:27,446
Detective, Miss Crock has told you
everything she knows.

231
00:19:27,527 --> 00:19:29,802
What do you mean?
She hasn't told me anything.

232
00:19:29,887 --> 00:19:32,037
Sir, if it makes you happy...

233
00:19:32,207 --> 00:19:35,643
...you go right ahead
and find Willard Fillmore.

234
00:19:37,247 --> 00:19:38,760
As for me...

235
00:19:39,807 --> 00:19:41,479
...it's time for my nap.

236
00:19:45,367 --> 00:19:48,439
Sources say that Fillmore
moved to Pittsburgh at the age ofsix.

237
00:19:48,527 --> 00:19:50,722
Here's the thing. I hardly knew Willard.

238
00:19:50,807 --> 00:19:55,756
Police say ifyou have any information,
call the Piehunt Hotline at 1-800--

239
00:19:55,847 --> 00:19:59,044
-How did this get so big?
-Rusty, we gotta turn ourselves in.

240
00:19:59,127 --> 00:20:00,845
How? They think you're the victim.

241
00:20:00,927 --> 00:20:04,124
Shit! You have to be really dumb
to accidentally kidnap yourself.

242
00:20:04,287 --> 00:20:07,484
Wait a minute.
This is all gonna get pinned on me!

243
00:20:07,647 --> 00:20:10,605
You gotta get un-kidnapped!
You gotta escape!

244
00:20:10,887 --> 00:20:14,516
The kidnappers go out to dinner,
you chew through the ropes, you get away.

245
00:20:14,607 --> 00:20:17,838
Yeah, that's good.
That's good, but it should be real.

246
00:20:18,527 --> 00:20:21,917
There was a struggle
and l got all bruised and beat up!

247
