-What's going on here?
-We were just turning down the sheets.

733
00:54:40,567 --> 00:54:42,205
Where's Miss Crock?

734
00:54:42,287 --> 00:54:45,199
Who are you?
What's that note in your hand?

735
00:54:51,127 --> 00:54:52,924
What'd you do that for?

736
00:54:53,567 --> 00:54:55,046
l was scared.

737
00:54:56,127 --> 00:54:58,960
-What do we do now?
-Run!

738
00:55:00,487 --> 00:55:04,116
-This is so bad!
-Jesus forgive me!

739
00:55:12,127 --> 00:55:13,685
Help. Police.

740
00:55:14,287 --> 00:55:16,084
That stupid Grover!

741
00:55:16,167 --> 00:55:18,556
What kind of kidnapper
uses his own stationery?

742
00:55:18,647 --> 00:55:21,115
You know, they're gonna catch him,
and when they do...

743
00:55:21,207 --> 00:55:23,641
...he's gonna blab all about us!

744
00:55:29,167 --> 00:55:31,158
They're hunting us down!

745
00:55:35,767 --> 00:55:37,439
Stop! This is the police!

746
00:55:37,567 --> 00:55:40,400
-Well, no shit!
-Let's jump that fence!

747
00:55:41,607 --> 00:55:44,724
-l'm getting a charley horse!
-l gotta start working out!

748
00:55:51,287 --> 00:55:53,596
Freeze! You're under arrest!

749
00:55:56,047 --> 00:55:57,924
Details are sketchy,
butin a twiststranger than bizarre...

750
00:55:58,007 --> 00:56:00,726
...Miss Virginia Crock herself
has been kidnapped.

751
00:56:01,727 --> 00:56:02,637
Oh, my God!

752
00:56:03,967 --> 00:56:06,037
Snowball. Baby, let me in!

753
00:56:06,687 --> 00:56:08,279
Open up!

754
00:56:09,967 --> 00:56:12,800
-Have you heard the news?
-Yes, l know. lt's terrible.

755
00:56:15,967 --> 00:56:17,923
-What are we gonna do?
-l don't know.

756
00:56:18,007 --> 00:56:21,044
-But this is not our fault.
-You said it wouldn't hurt anyone!

757
00:56:21,127 --> 00:56:24,005
You said if we switched the money
nothing would happen.

758
00:56:24,087 --> 00:56:25,600
The kidnappers would be stuck!

759
00:56:25,687 --> 00:56:28,645
All l meant was
that they couldn't complain to the police.

760
00:56:28,727 --> 00:56:30,319
Now we've pissed them off!

761
00:56:30,407 --> 00:56:33,160
You deserve that money.
She's been a figurehead for years.

762
00:56:33,527 --> 00:56:34,118
Oh, stop it!

763
00:56:34,207 --> 00:56:36,721
You're the only one
holding that bakery together.

764
00:56:36,807 --> 00:56:38,798
l had to. She's out of her mind.

765
00:56:38,887 --> 00:56:43,802
Exactly. So, why don't we
just let the kidnappers keep her?

766
00:56:46,487 --> 00:56:48,364
Get me out of here!

767
00:56:48,447 --> 00:56:51,883
The pain! I got a medical condition.

768
00:56:52,167 --> 00:56:54,044
All right, Fillmore. Time to talk.

769
00:56:54,127 --> 00:56:56,197
My dick hurts!

770
00:57:00,327 --> 00:57:04,240
l want the truth. What's your connection
to Rusty P. Hayes?

771
00:57:04,327 --> 00:57:07,956
l've known Rusty my whole life.
Our mothers were in church choir together.

772
00:57:08,127 --> 00:57:10,960
l don't even know this chauffeur guy,
all right?

773
00:57:11,047 --> 00:57:13,925
The first time l seen him
was in my restaurant, two weeks ago.

774
00:57:14,007 --> 00:57:16,521
Last night, like every week,
l called up Rusty...

775
00:57:16,607 --> 00:57:19,360
...and told him to come
and watch Monday Night Football.

776
00:57:19,447 --> 00:57:21,438
Last night was Thursday.

777
00:57:22,327 --> 00:57:25,603
Yeah. l'm sorry. lt wasn't
Monday Night Football. lt was Oprah.

778
00:57:25,687 --> 00:57:28,645
Last night, l get this call
to make a delivery...

779
00:57:28,807 --> 00:57:30,718
...to this Wilbur guy.

780
00:57:30,887 --> 00:57:33,037
You mean, Willard.

781
00:57:33,127 --> 00:57:35,402
Yeah, right. Willard.

782
00:57:35,527 --> 00:57:40,203
So anyway, l drive up to this mansion
in my chicken delivery truck.

783
00:57:40,327 --> 00:57:44,764
You know your truck was impounded
at the airport earlier that day?

784
00:57:44,847 --> 00:57:46,405
lt was?

785
00:57:47,127 --> 00:57:50,039
Yeah, right. No, l was on foot.

786
00:57:50,287 --> 00:57:53,836
So anyway, the doorbell rings,
and it's the kidnappers!

787
00:57:54,247 --> 00:57:57,000
So, they started chasing us.

788
00:57:57,087 --> 00:57:59,123
And then Miss Crock,
l remember she showed up.

789
00:57:59,207 --> 00:58:03,200
She ran in, and she'd just been taking
a bath, so she was nude.

790
00:58:03,287 --> 00:58:05,403
Of course, naturally, this upset everybody.

791
00:58:05,487 --> 00:58:07,717
Gunshots started going off, man.

792
00:58:07,807 --> 00:58:10,241
The windows was exploding,
l heard screaming.

793
00:58:10,327 --> 00:58:12,795
So, l run to my truck as fast as l can.

794
00:58:13,087 --> 00:58:16,966
l mean, l run away because l was scared.

795
00:58:17,047 --> 00:58:21,962
Chip Oswald says you hit him
over the head with a desk lamp.

796
00:58:23,687 --> 00:58:25,837
No, he's mistaken.

797
00:58:26,087 --> 00:58:28,123
He's mistaken. That was not me.

798
00:58:28,207 --> 00:58:31,836
So, Rusty's got this desk lamp
and he's beating the hell out of Chip.

799
00:58:31,927 --> 00:58:34,760
And, he's pounding him and pounding him.

800
00:58:34,927 --> 00:58:37,043
Then l say:

801
00:58:37,127 --> 00:58:40,961
''Rusty, that's not the kidnappers.
That's Chip!''

802
00:58:41,247 --> 00:58:44,239
That's when the cops showed up
and they distracted everybody...

803
00:58:45,007 --> 00:58:46,645
...and the kidnappers got away.

804
00:58:47,727 --> 00:58:49,763
One final question.

805
00:58:50,647 --> 00:58:53,605
Let's forget all this other crap.

806
00:58:54,327 --> 00:58:56,602
Where is Miss Crock?

807
00:58:57,247 --> 00:58:58,043
l don't know.

808
00:58:59,247 --> 00:59:00,919
Who is Miss Crock?

809
00:59:04,047 --> 00:59:05,526
Come on. Open your mouth.

810
00:59:05,607 --> 00:59:07,677
Come on. You want some food, Blackie?

811
00:59:07,767 --> 00:59:09,359
Eat some dinner.

812
00:59:09,887 --> 00:59:12,355
Eat it, Blackie. lt's good. Look.

813
00:59:13,127 --> 00:59:15,436
-Come on, Blackie.
-His name is Muffin.

814
00:59:15,607 --> 00:59:17,245
lt is not Blackie.

815
00:59:17,727 --> 00:59:19,046
Shut up!

816
00:59:19,287 --> 00:59:23,280
The dog's name is what l say it is
until somebody takes you off my hands.

817
00:59:23,367 --> 00:59:26,359
The sooner the better, Poopy.
The sooner the better!

818
00:59:26,447 --> 00:59:28,642
-Yeah, go on!
-''Yeah, go on!''

819
00:59:30,367 --> 00:59:31,686
Help!

820
00:59:33,207 --> 00:59:36,756
That's my favorite TV program.
We're gonna watch it, Blackie.

821
00:59:36,847 --> 00:59:39,919
This is it. Look at that. See that?

822
00:59:40,687 --> 00:59:42,040
Hawaii Five-0.

823
00:59:42,967 --> 00:59:46,482
-What have we got, Danno?
-Klaus Marburg. West German passport.

824
00:59:46,607 --> 00:59:47,835
-How bad?
-How bad?

825
00:59:47,927 --> 00:59:50,487
-Pretty bad. Went right through him.
-Any witnesses?

826
00:59:50,567 --> 00:59:52,444
-Any witnesses?
-Yeah, lots of them.

827
00:59:52,687 --> 00:59:54,564
-Only one shot?
-Only one shot?

828
00:59:54,647 --> 00:59:55,443
Just one.

829
00:59:57,007 --> 00:59:59,316
He was hitjust after
he stepped off the ramp.

830
00:59:59,407 --> 01:00:02,604
Steve, take a look. Finished.

831
01:00:03,847 --> 01:00:06,680
What is your obsession with that guy?

832
01:00:07,647 --> 01:00:09,160
lt's Jack Lord!

833
01:00:09,287 --> 01:00:12,085
l'm the vice president
of his national fan club.

834
01:00:12,487 --> 01:00:14,205
Clam up, will you?

835
01:00:19,167 --> 01:00:20,998
Hey! What are you, crazy?

836
01:00:23,127 --> 01:00:25,118
The show's not over yet.

837
01:00:25,287 --> 01:00:26,925
Give me that.

838
01:00:30,727 --> 01:00:33,525
-Excuse me. May I have your attention?
-Oh, my God.

839
01:00:33,607 --> 01:00:36,041
I'm pleased to announce
that Miss Crock's Bakery...

840
01:00:36,127 --> 01:00:38,516
...is now merging
with Copenhagen Snak Food.

841
01:00:38,727 --> 01:00:41,241
-What the hell are you talking about?
-Additionally...

842
01:00:41,367 --> 01:00:44,757
...in accordance with Miss Crock's policy
regarding kidnapping...

843
01:00:44,847 --> 01:00:48,044
...we will notpay the ransom.

844
01:00:48,167 --> 01:00:51,842
I know Miss Crock will be proud of us
standing behind herlike this.

845
01:00:51,927 --> 01:00:55,317
Hey, wait a minute.
l'm gonna get screwed on this deal.

846
01:00:58,127 --> 01:01:00,163
That's two dozen anthuriums.

847
01:01:07,367 --> 01:01:08,243
What?

848
01:01:08,687 --> 01:01:11,565
What did l do? Jesus, Mary and Joseph.

849
01:01:11,647 --> 01:01:13,717
l swear l'm innocent!

850
01:01:14,127 --> 01:01:15,879
No, please! Don't!

851
01:01:15,967 --> 01:01:19,403
-Who's the crybaby?
-We just busted the guy.

852
01:01:19,527 --> 01:01:23,315
He was trying to pass the marked bills
from the Fillmore kidnapping.

853
01:01:23,407 --> 01:01:24,999
Well, what do you know?

854
01:01:25,087 --> 01:01:27,726
The brains behind the operation.

855
01:01:28,087 --> 01:01:29,486
Get me Fillmore and Hayes!

856
01:01:29,567 --> 01:01:31,956
-Don't tell them about Grover.
-Why not?

857
01:01:32,047 --> 01:01:34,766
Things are bad enough
without us getting blamed...

858
01:01:34,847 --> 01:01:37,122
...for killing that old midget
at the wax museum.

859
01:01:38,247 --> 01:01:40,681
-Maybe we should tell them the truth.
-Yeah, right.

860
01:01:40,767 --> 01:01:44,043
Like they'll believe it started
'cause we kidnapped Muffin's turd.

861
01:01:44,887 --> 01:01:47,526
There you are. Get in here! Sit down!

862
01:01:51,727 --> 01:01:54,287
The days of dicking Dewey are over.

863
01:01:54,527 --> 01:01:57,963
We found the kidnapper.
Your partner extraordinaire...

864
01:01:58,047 --> 01:01:59,685
...he's in our custody.

865
01:01:59,767 --> 01:02:02,201
So, tell me all about Roger.

866
01:02:03,447 --> 01:02:04,277
Who?

867
01:02:04,767 --> 01:02:06,325
Oh, no.

868
01:02:06,767 --> 01:02:08,564
You can't play those games anymore.

869
01:02:08,687 --> 01:02:10,643
We nailed him with marked bills.

870
01:02:10,727 --> 01:02:12,922
All that $5 million was traceable.

871
01:02:13,007 --> 01:02:14,998
What $5 million? Miss Crock never paid.

872
01:02:16,967 --> 01:02:19,197
What do you mean, she never paid?

873
01:02:23,127 --> 01:02:24,196
l don't know.

874
01:02:24,287 --> 01:02:26,596
You just said Miss Crock never paid.

875
01:02:26,687 --> 01:02:28,325
What do you mean, she never paid?

876
01:02:28,407 --> 01:02:31,126
-l didn't say that.
-You did. l heard you say that.

877
01:02:31,207 --> 01:02:32,845
You said, ''Miss Crock never paid.''

878
01:02:32,927 --> 01:02:34,599
l wanna know what you meant by that.

879
01:02:36,287 --> 01:02:38,562
-l don't know.
-What did you mean by that?

880
01:02:38,647 --> 01:02:41,241
What did you mean,
Miss Crock never paid?

881
01:02:41,327 --> 01:02:42,806
What did he mean by that?

882
01:02:47,007 --> 01:02:49,885
What the hell are you doing?
That man's a cop!

883
01:02:50,647 --> 01:02:52,126
l was scared.

884
01:02:52,287 --> 01:02:55,882
Every time you're scared,
you hit a guy with a desk lamp!

885
01:02:57,807 --> 01:02:59,365
l'm getting out of here.

886
01:03:06,647 --> 01:03:09,320
-Who gave you the marked money?
-l don't know!

887
01:03:09,407 --> 01:03:12,046
lt was change in a restaurant.

888
01:03:12,247 --> 01:03:15,523
lf you don't tell us,
you're spending three years in hard labor.

889
01:03:17,047 --> 01:03:18,878
lt was Chip Oswald.

890
01:03:25,607 --> 01:03:27,040
Come on!

891
01:03:35,647 --> 01:03:39,003
Willard, this is a cop car.
Should we really be taking a cop car?

892
01:03:39,927 --> 01:03:41,440
l'm gonna kill you!

893
01:03:42,367 --> 01:03:44,517
Put your ass to the gas! Go!

894
01:03:48,687 --> 01:03:51,281
-Where are we going?
-l don't know!

895
01:03:56,687 --> 01:03:59,121
Shit. We're not making things any better.

896
01:03:59,207 --> 01:04:01,801
We gotta find Miss Crock and Grover
and clear this up.

897
01:04:01,887 --> 01:04:04,117
How we gonna do that?
We know nothing about him.

898
01:04:04,207 --> 01:04:07,756
We don't know where he lives, how
to reach him. He's a complete mystery.

899
01:04:07,847 --> 01:04:10,281
Hold on. l got an idea.

900
01:04:12,567 --> 01:04:14,319
Directory assistance. What city?

901
01:04:14,407 --> 01:04:16,967
Pittsburgh. Grover Cleaver.

902
01:04:17,047 --> 01:04:19,641
-Is that a business or residence?
-Residence.

903
01:04:19,727 --> 01:04:22,287
-Is that Kleaver with a ''K''?
-No, with a ''C''...

904
01:04:22,367 --> 01:04:24,323
...like ''cupcake.''

905
01:04:26,167 --> 01:04:28,362
Thank you. Press 1 to be connected.

906
01:04:29,567 --> 01:04:30,317
Got it.

907
01:04:33,327 --> 01:04:36,763
Aloha. You've reached
the Jack Lord Fan Club.

908
01:04:37,047 --> 01:04:40,164
-For membership, send $25...
-l got the Jack Lord Fan Club.

909
01:04:40,247 --> 01:04:41,965
...to the Jack Lord Fan Club.

910
01:04:42,047 --> 01:04:44,766
-Attention: Grover Cleaver.
-Wait! lt's Grover!

911
01:04:44,847 --> 01:04:47,156
He lives at 910 Mabley Terrace.

912
01:04:47,247 --> 01:04:50,319
Mabley Terrace?
That's a shitty neighborhood.

913
01:04:55,687 --> 01:04:57,006
Damn it! Turn around!

914
01:05:07,527 --> 01:05:09,085
We got away!

915
01:05:14,047 --> 01:05:17,835
As you can see from oursky-cam
they are traveling in a stolen police car.

916
01:05:17,927 --> 01:05:20,487
Again, to recap for those viewers
just tuning in...

917
01:05:20,567 --> 01:05:24,480
...less than 15 minutes ago the two
key suspects in the Crock kidnapping...

918
01:05:24,567 --> 01:05:26,603
...escaped from a downtown police station.

919
01:05:26,687 --> 01:05:28,917
We'll stay with this story
until its conclusion.

920
01:05:38,967 --> 01:05:41,435
Here we go. l got it all.

921
01:05:42,007 --> 01:05:43,918
Here it is.

922
01:05:45,127 --> 01:05:47,322
One box of Fixodent.

923
01:05:49,447 --> 01:05:53,042
One bag of prunes for the old chute.

924
01:05:54,447 --> 01:05:57,519
And four pounds of lamb and rice...

925
01:05:57,607 --> 01:05:58,835
...Dog Chow!

926
01:05:58,927 --> 01:06:00,280
That's for you.

927
01:06:01,367 --> 01:06:02,880
Where's my Ben-Gay?

928
01:06:02,967 --> 01:06:07,165
You forgot my Ben-Gay, didn't you?
You know my muscles get sore!

929
01:06:07,247 --> 01:06:10,159
''You know my muscles get sore.''
Zip it, you nag!

930
01:06:11,007 --> 01:06:13,919
l wish l never met that dang chauffeur.

931
01:06:14,127 --> 01:06:17,119
Come on. The first rule of life, Blackie:

932
01:06:17,287 --> 01:06:18,879
''Never do no favors.''

933
01:06:18,967 --> 01:06:21,879
You call kidnapping a man
doing him a favor?

934
01:06:22,687 --> 01:06:25,804
l didn't kidnap that guy.
He kidnapped himself.

935
01:06:28,087 --> 01:06:29,645
What did you say?

936
01:06:37,727 --> 01:06:39,763
You ain't gonna take me alive!

937
01:06:52,887 --> 01:06:53,524
Grover!

938
01:06:58,087 --> 01:06:59,998
-Jesus Christ!
-Why is he shooting at us?

939
01:07:00,087 --> 01:07:02,237
He thinks we're the police!

940
01:07:03,807 --> 01:07:08,039
Grover, we are not the police!
We are not the police!

941
01:07:09,407 --> 01:07:11,921
Try to fool stupid Grover, huh?

942
01:07:12,007 --> 01:07:13,360
l'll show ya!

943
01:07:19,487 --> 01:07:22,365
-Grover, it's us!
-Don't shoot!

944
01:07:23,767 --> 01:07:25,883
lt's you guys. Come on up!

945
01:07:26,607 --> 01:07:28,199
Hurry up! Hurry up!

946
01:07:30,287 --> 01:07:33,962
-Any word yet on that car?
-Yeah, it's been spotted on Mabley Terrace.

947
01:07:34,087 --> 01:07:36,647
Mabley Terrace? Jesus.

948
01:07:37,247 --> 01:07:38,805
l'll need some backup. Let's go!

949
01:07:39,167 --> 01:07:43,046
Grover, you have to let Miss Crock go.
Too much shit's going on.

950
01:07:43,127 --> 01:07:46,039
No way! l'm out $18 for groceries.

951
01:07:46,127 --> 01:07:47,276
What?

952
01:07:47,927 --> 01:07:50,680
-Here's $20, all right?
-l can't break no $20.

953
01:07:50,767 --> 01:07:53,156
-Keep the change!
-All right.

954
01:07:55,687 --> 01:08:00,363
-Miss Crock, we're here to rescue you.
-How dare you kidnap yourself!

955
01:08:01,447 --> 01:08:04,245
You tried to swindle me?

956
01:08:04,527 --> 01:08:07,644
l am going to have your ass!

957
01:08:08,007 --> 01:08:10,760
-Miss Crock, l'm sorry.
-What nerve!

958
01:08:11,167 --> 01:08:13,317
After all l've done for you.

959
01:08:13,407 --> 01:08:17,002
l was under a lot of pressure, and l....

960
01:08:18,127 --> 01:08:21,119
After all you've done for me?

961
01:08:25,327 --> 01:08:28,558
Willard Fillmore,
the building is surrounded!

962
01:08:28,647 --> 01:08:31,605
What exactly, Miss Crock,
did you ever do for me?

963
01:08:31,687 --> 01:08:34,963
l've been your slave for 15 years!
l worked my butt off!

964
01:08:35,047 --> 01:08:38,676
And then, when l got kidnapped,
you wouldn't even pay the ransom money!

965
01:08:38,887 --> 01:08:41,242
Well, after all, you...

966
01:08:41,607 --> 01:08:44,280
-...were just a hired servant.
-Hired....

967
01:08:45,047 --> 01:08:48,483
Well, does a hired servant
watch TV with you when you're lonely?

968
01:08:48,687 --> 01:08:53,124
Does a hired servant read to you
that time you broke your glasses?

969
01:08:53,527 --> 01:08:57,122
Does a hired servant visit you
in the hospital when nobody else does?

970
01:08:57,487 --> 01:08:59,876
l did everything my father would've.

971
01:09:03,887 --> 01:09:05,161
Not everything.

972
01:09:07,207 --> 01:09:10,756
Your father was, a very special man.

973
01:09:11,847 --> 01:09:15,760
He provided extra services.

974
01:09:18,127 --> 01:09:20,004
Oh, my God.

