01:09:20,127 --> 01:09:23,119
Your dad didn't say,
''Stick with Miss Crock. You'll get ahead.''

976
01:09:23,207 --> 01:09:26,643
He said, ''Stick with Miss Crock
and you'll get head.''

977
01:09:26,727 --> 01:09:30,117
Would you butt out? We're talking here!

978
01:09:30,207 --> 01:09:31,720
Yuck!

979
01:09:32,927 --> 01:09:35,361
Let's move!

980
01:09:39,487 --> 01:09:41,637
-Can you see them?
-They're on the third floor.

981
01:09:42,447 --> 01:09:43,402
Oh, man!

982
01:09:43,487 --> 01:09:45,523
That's why l couldn't compare to my dad?

983
01:09:45,607 --> 01:09:48,758
Now, don't be silly. lt's just that...

984
01:09:48,847 --> 01:09:51,998
...your father was very gifted.

985
01:09:52,087 --> 01:09:55,045
-That's some big shoes to fill.
-l don't wanna hear this!

986
01:09:55,127 --> 01:09:58,085
Man, you must've been a total let down.

987
01:09:58,167 --> 01:10:00,635
No wonder she ransomed you
with an empty suitcase.

988
01:10:00,727 --> 01:10:03,036
That suitcase wasn't empty.

989
01:10:04,487 --> 01:10:05,806
l paid every cent.

990
01:10:05,887 --> 01:10:08,685
Then why do Roger and Chip
have the money?

991
01:10:08,767 --> 01:10:11,042
Roger and Chip?

992
01:10:13,927 --> 01:10:17,602
Stop! Don't shoot!
They're stupid and confused!

993
01:10:17,687 --> 01:10:19,996
Position! Move out!

994
01:10:20,087 --> 01:10:22,396
-l'm going in.
-Come on!

995
01:10:22,847 --> 01:10:24,519
l can't believe it.

996
01:10:24,727 --> 01:10:29,721
l can't believe Chip shafted me.

997
01:10:30,287 --> 01:10:31,800
l can't believe you came through.

998
01:10:31,887 --> 01:10:33,400
Beaver team, move in! Go!

999
01:10:37,527 --> 01:10:39,358
lt's like an army out there.

1000
01:10:40,607 --> 01:10:43,758
l'm on parole for mail fraud. l gotta hide.

1001
01:10:50,367 --> 01:10:52,323
-How'd you get in there, man?
-l mean...

1002
01:10:52,407 --> 01:10:54,204
-Come on, Grover!
-...l...

1003
01:10:54,287 --> 01:10:58,838
...took care of all of Chip's gambling debts.

1004
01:10:59,407 --> 01:11:02,956
l paid for all his methadone treatments.

1005
01:11:04,527 --> 01:11:06,802
l guess we both got the big screw.

1006
01:11:08,207 --> 01:11:10,118
Come on, Grover!

1007
01:11:11,127 --> 01:11:13,482
Don't move! Hayes and Fillmore...

1008
01:11:13,567 --> 01:11:16,923
...you're under arrest, again,
for the abduction of Virginia Crock.

1009
01:11:17,007 --> 01:11:19,202
And this time, it's gonna stick!

1010
01:11:21,287 --> 01:11:23,517
You clod.

1011
01:11:23,967 --> 01:11:26,356
They didn't kidnap me.

1012
01:11:26,447 --> 01:11:28,881
They rescued me.

1013
01:11:29,287 --> 01:11:33,565
lf Willard hadn't shown up,
l'd be dead and buried in this hellhole!

1014
01:11:34,047 --> 01:11:37,517
l don't understand.
Then who's the kidnapper?

1015
01:11:41,927 --> 01:11:44,725
First, l wanna upgrade the assembly line.

1016
01:11:44,807 --> 01:11:47,446
Toss out minced meat.

1017
01:11:47,567 --> 01:11:49,398
Bring in vanilla custard.

1018
01:11:51,247 --> 01:11:53,761
Then, l'm gonna mix
strawberry into the rhubarb.

1019
01:11:58,047 --> 01:12:00,481
Freeze! You're under arrest.

1020
01:12:01,927 --> 01:12:03,280
Chip Oswald...

1021
01:12:03,367 --> 01:12:07,246
...you are under arrest for the kidnappings
of Willard Fillmore and Virginia Crock.

1022
01:12:07,327 --> 01:12:10,637
That is ridiculous! How dare you!

1023
01:12:10,807 --> 01:12:13,162
l demand you leave my house!

1024
01:12:19,167 --> 01:12:21,397
Put on your pants. You're going to jail.

1025
01:12:21,767 --> 01:12:24,042
All right, let's get them hands
behind your back.

1026
01:12:25,247 --> 01:12:27,841
Oh, my God! lt's the new Village People.

1027
01:12:28,847 --> 01:12:30,838
-You're all crazy!
-Put down that gun!

1028
01:12:30,927 --> 01:12:33,566
-l'm not going back to prison!
-What do you mean...

1029
01:12:33,647 --> 01:12:35,205
-...''back''?
-Up yours!

1030
01:12:35,287 --> 01:12:39,724
l've got nothing from all of those years
of suffering, working for you!

1031
01:12:39,807 --> 01:12:42,002
-Nobody does.
-Stay out of this!

1032
01:12:42,967 --> 01:12:44,958
l'll see you all in hell!

1033
01:12:45,487 --> 01:12:48,399
l'll slice you and l'll dice you...

1034
01:12:48,487 --> 01:12:51,285
...and l'll bake you all into meat pies!

1035
01:12:58,847 --> 01:13:01,407
Well, it's an ugly ending,
but the case is solved.

1036
01:13:01,607 --> 01:13:04,246
l knew he was the kidnapper
the whole time.

1037
01:13:04,447 --> 01:13:07,484
Never trust a black man named Chip.

1038
01:13:14,007 --> 01:13:16,202
This is so beautiful.

1039
01:13:17,007 --> 01:13:19,965
-l could spend the rest of my life here.
-Yeah.

1040
01:13:20,047 --> 01:13:22,959
And we found a place
where almost everyone speaks English.

1041
01:13:33,767 --> 01:13:36,076
There's my juicy, succulent chicken.
Come here.

1042
01:13:36,887 --> 01:13:39,321
-How's business, baby?
-Great, Rusty.

1043
01:13:39,407 --> 01:13:41,284
You guys got a package.

1044
01:13:44,207 --> 01:13:45,242
Look.

1045
01:13:45,647 --> 01:13:47,160
lt's from Miss Crock.

1046
01:13:47,767 --> 01:13:49,519
What did she send?

1047
01:13:52,847 --> 01:13:56,362
-Check it out. lt's an Armani suit.
-And there's a letter.

1048
01:14:00,487 --> 01:14:04,560
''Dear Willard, I hope you're enjoying
your retirement money.

1049
01:14:04,647 --> 01:14:08,799
''Here's a suityou can wear
when you graduate from U.S.C.

1050
01:14:09,127 --> 01:14:12,676
''Back in Pittsburgh,
I decided not to sell the company.

1051
01:14:12,767 --> 01:14:16,476
''And I have a new man in my life.

1052
01:14:17,207 --> 01:14:19,163
''Grover's quite special.

1053
01:14:19,887 --> 01:14:23,675
''He's a little slow,
but he does what he's told.

1054
01:14:24,007 --> 01:14:27,124
''So, thanks again forintroducing us.

1055
01:14:27,487 --> 01:14:30,285
''Your everlasting friend, Virginia.''